The following code is meant to create and use a lambda that adds a local offset. What is the bug?

```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <functional>
std::function<int(int)> make_adder(int offset) {
    int local = offset;
    return [&local](int x) { return x + local; };
}
int main() {
    auto add5 = make_adder(5);
    std::cout << add5(10) << '\n'; // intended: 15
}
```
